review_blob: Meh.  After the build-up this got from the beer-store guy I was really disappointed.  A one-dimensional beer - and not for me.
Delicious!  Tart, without the vinegary taste of some other sour ales - definately mellowed by the oak-aging process.  Low carbonation, no head.  DO OVER!
Creamy, yeasty and mellow with a low fizz.  A bit tart and totally yummy!  Definately a do-over.
My other favorite pumpkin beer!  This one tastes more like pumpkin pie spice than like pumpkin.  An effervescent desert-like treat!
One of my two favorite pumpkin beers for totally different reasons.  This one has a BIG roasted pumpkin taste with subtle spices.  Low carbonation and a nice lingering taste.  Yummy!
Nice aroma and a great everyday beer.  Light in flavor, medium carbonation, pretty color.
A very avereage beer.  Slighly flat wwith a dark brown color.  There was absolutely no hint whatsoever of cocont.  Disappointing.

This is a phenomenal creamy stout - and hard as hell to get!  It has very complex flavors - coffee, maple, malts.
